<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880812-0030 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Northwestern Steel andamp; Wire Co. </HL><SO> </SO><IN> TNM MIN </IN><TEXT>   Northwestern Steel andamp; Wire Co. said shareholders approved a sweetened buy-out offer of $187.7 million, or $25 a share, in cash and securities from an investment group including certain senior managers.    As previously reported, shareholders will receive $19 in cash, plus $6 face amount of 13% subordinated notes due 1997 of the surviving company.    The Sterling, Ill., steel concern said the transaction is expected to be completed early next week.    Yesterday in New York Stock Exchange composite trading, Northwestern shares closed at $24.625, up 87.5 cents. </TEXT></DOC>